at| 

There is 1 exception to this rule to bid  2@C 
If you have a good 6 card major of your own, you may bid it. But it had better be pretty good!


If LHO bids over the double, you should find out what they're playing. 
Almost every pair has some counter to DONT, be it Lebensohl, or stolen bids or snapdragon or systems on...
So you'll bid appropriately.  
Most of the time, you'll pass and let pard make the final mistake  :)  
But also, most of the time, RHO will pass too. 

If partner makes a ^*U2-suited^*N DONT call:|
